1.10	Khaplu	Khaplu	Khaplu (Khapalu, Balti: ) is the administrative capital of the Ghangche District of Gilgit-Baltistan. Lying 103 km (64 mi) east of Skardu town, it was the second-largest kingdom in old Baltistan. It guarded the trade route to Ladakh along the Shyok River.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/66/Pakistan_location_map.svg/300px-Pakistan_location_map.svg.png
